quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  42,23,"This is the good news God gives to His worshipers who believe and do good deeds.Say, \"I do not ask you any wage for it, except affection due to kin.\" Whoever does a good deed, We will increase it for him. God is Ever Forgiving and Most Appreciative"
  42,24,"Or do they say, \"He falsely claimed lies about God?\" If God so willed, He could have sealed your heart, exterminated falsehood and confirmed the Truth with His Words. He has full Knowledge of what is in the hearts"
  42,25,"It is He who accepts repentance from his worshipers and forgives bad deeds, He knows what you do"
  42,26,He answers those who have believed and done good deeds and increases for them out of His grace. But the unbelievers will have a severe punishment
  42,27,"Were God to expand provision to His worshipers, they would have committed tyranny on earth. But He sends down whatever He wills in due measures. He is, well Acquainted and Fully Aware of His worshipers"
  42,28,"It is He who sends down the rain after they have lost hope and unfolds His mercy. He is the Protector, the Praiseworthy"
  42,29,"Among His signs is the creation of the heavens and earth and the creatures He has spread throughout them: He is Able to gather them together if He so wishes"
  42,30,"Whatever disaster strikes you, It is for what your hands have done; Yet He forgives much"
  42,31,On earth you will not be beyond God's reach. You do not have any protector or helper besides God